<TEXT>
actor ken murray whose 30year career 
spanned the vaudeville stage and films including the 1962 motion 
picture the man who shot liberty valance died wednesday he 
was 85 
the beverly hills resident died of natural causes at st joseph 
medical center in burbank said his publicist jeffrey godsick 
murray was born don court in new york city in 1903 
his film career began from the 1930s and continued until the 
late 1960s he is best remembered for his longrunning hollywood 
stage appearances in ken murrays blackout which ran from 1942 
to 1949 
he produced bill amp coo a featurelength fantasy film about 
birds that received a special academy award in 1947 for novel and 
entertaining use of the film medium 
he also starred produced and directed televisions the ken 
murray show other television credits include hollywood without 
makeup hollywood my home town and el coyote 
his motion picture debut was in halfmarriage in 1929 other 
films included leathernecking youre a sweetheart 1937 
a night at earl carrolls 1940 juke box jenny 1942 
son of flubber 1963 the power 1968 and ken murrays 
shooting stars a homemade 16mm film murray shot recording the 
daytoday lives of his contemporaries the candid scenes have been 
internationally distributed as classic vignettes of the golden age 
of hollywood 
murray also wrote books including the body merchant life 
on a pogo stick and the golden days of san simeon 
</TEXT>
