the second this fire season directly attributed to a blaze 
hutton a federal bureau of land management employee was at the 
edge of a meadow with other firefighters when the dead tree fell on 
him from behind said fire information officer lynn young 
hutton apparently died instantly young said the firefighters 
body was taken to a hospital in this town east of yellowstone 
a falling tree killed a firefighter in montana last month 
in september and august three people died when helicopters 
involved in firefighting crashed in wyoming and washington state 
forest fires have burned more than 4 million acres in the west 
this year in what federal officials have called the worst fire 
season in 30 years 
