rule within 90 days a home ministry spokesman said on condition of 
anonymity 
the convictions and death sentences for both men has been upheld 
and the supreme court has rejected their appeals the conviction 
and death sentence of a third man balbir singh was overturned in 
august for lack of evidence 
mrs gandhi was shot and killed in the garden of her home on 
oct 31 1984 by two of her sikh bodyguards satwant singh and 
beant singh 
both were involved in a gun battle with other security guards 
minutes after the assassination and beant singh died of bullet 
wounds 
the two are not related singh which means lion in the punjabi 
language is part of every sikhs name by doctrine of the faith 
kehar singh beant singhs maternal uncle was arrested on nov 
30 1984 and charged with conspiracy in the case 
the assassination was apparently in revenge for an army raid 
mrs gandhi ordered four months earlier on the golden temple the 
holiest sikh shrine to counter separatist militants entrenched 
inside at least 1200 died in the raid most of them sikhs 
after an eightmonth trial in a makeshift courtroom at tihar 
central jail satwant singh was convicted of assassinating mrs 
gandhi kehar singh and balbir singh were found guilty of aiding 
the conspiracy 
the delhi high court upheld the convictions and death sentences 
on dec 3 1986 the supreme court on aug 3 also confirmed the 
death sentences of satwant singh and kehar singh but acquitted 
balbir singh 
