<TEXT>
the house refused wednesday to abolish the 
muchcriticized federal agency created to manage and sell off the 
worst assets of insolvent savings institutions 
the house voted 247130 to approve the measure under the 
procedure used however twothirds of those voting had to be in 
favor of the legislation for passage and the house failed to reach 
that margin by five votes 
even if the house had approved the bill there was little chance 
for passage by the senate which hasnt considered such legislation 
the federal assets disposition administration a quasipublic 
organization was formed by the federal home loan bank in 1985 to 
assist the federal savings and loan insurance corp in the 
management and disposition of acquired assets 
lawmakers have accused it of favoritism conflicts of interest 
and mismanagement of the 39 billion in loans and real estate in 
its care 
fada was criticized bitterly for paying salaries as high as 
250000 annually cloaking its activities in secret and failing to 
dispose of many of the assets placed in its custody 
the house banking committee approved the bill on oct 4 by a 
vote of 428 with all the negative votes coming from republicans 
who see the legislation as a political measure rather than 
substantive action 
the legislation would have given the bank board 60 days to close 
fada and limit severence pay for employees to about 4700 or 
three weeks salary rather than the four months pay pledged by 
the agency early this year 
the bill similar to a section of the omnibus banking 
legislation approved by the house in august would have assigned 
fadas activities to fslic the government insurance fund that 
backs sampl deposits up to 100000 
reps paul kanjorski dpa and tom mcmillen dmd introduced 
the legislation 
rep fernand j st germain dri banking committee chairman 
and floor manager for the bill said in debate that his panel had 
been investigating fada for the past 15 months 
our findings clearly establish that this agency has become a 
wasteful bureaucracy lacing in accountability and providing an 
inefficient means of disposing of property acquired from failed 
savings and loan associations he said 
high salaries big expense accounts and cialike secrecy have 
become the agencys claims to fame during its threeyear 
existence 
