three of the capitals most prestigious press organizations died 
of cancer early wednesday at his maryland home 
warren 75 was former president of the national press club and 
the gridiron club and was once chairman of the standing committee 
of correspondents which regulates the congressional press 
galleries he had a 43year career as a washington journalist 
