the credit guarantees are supposed to be reserved for 
americangrown crops only although the agriculture department says 
it will provide them for the americangrown portion of a blended 
shipment if the foreignproduced portion does not exceed 25 percent 
of the entire package 
fourteen of 19 exporters monitored by federal investigators 
