it was terrifying i thought the ladder would never reach me i 
saw the smoke getting thicker and prayed i would get out in time 
col flavio fagundes of the rio de janeiro fire department said 
about 400 people were in the 1940sera building when fire broke 
out 
construction workers had been renovating the bottom three floors 
of the building at the intersection of rio branco and presidente 
vargas avenues said public security director helio saboya 
he said the blaze began on the first floor but the cause was 
still undetermined 
many workers escaped by crossing over to an adjoining building 
others climbed stairs to the roof to await rescue by police 
helicopters 
about 50 of us were working on the 10th floor when all of a 
sudden smoke started coming through the ventilating system bank 
employee antonio soares told the associated press the building 
safety rules tell you that in case of a fire to go down but when 
we got to the fourth floor everything was blocked because of 
construction work 
we went back to the eighth floor somebody found a big hammer 
and we smashed a hole in the wall and got through to the building 
next door 
