among more than 3000 rebels attacking from east west and north 
but gave no figures for either side the rebels said friday that 62 
soldiers died in the threeday battle and that 300 fled into uganda 
the fall of ikotos gives the rebels control over three towns 
that form a triangle around torit capital of east equatoria 
province 85 miles east of juba the largest city in the south 
liberation army fighters captured kialla and katire weeks ago 
the sudan times said street fighting was reported this week in 
torit and that the archbishop has been sending appeals for food and 
other relief supplies for the besieged populace 
this is my last message to you tabans message read 
according to the newspaper we implore you to pray for peace 
he said catholic agencies in his diocese have nothing else to 
