set up a disinformation hotline to prevent accusations against 
each others countries from escalating into worldwide propaganda 
campaigns charles z wick head of the us information agency 
said wednesday 
agreement to work toward the establishment of an early 
warning system to challenge disinformation was among the results 
of ussoviet information talks in moscow sept 2628 said wick 
wick gave few details of the proposed system in a national press 
club speech but later used the term hotline suggesting it 
would be a telecommunications link patterned after the 25yearold 
moscowwashington hotline intended to prevent accidental 
triggering of a superpower nuclear war 
the early warning system would be designed to give the 
united states a mechanism to challenge disinformation efforts 
before they become part of a worldwide campaign wick said 
the russians have curtailed dramatically circulation of 
disinformation and extreme false or unsubstantiated charges 
against the united states since last decembers summit between 
president reagan and soviet leader mikhail s gorbachev said wick 
but exceptions continue he added recalling an official moscow 
radio broadcast he heard a few days ago about western countries 
buying children from impoverished south american countries and 
treating them as slaves 
i couldnt believe my ears we are going to try the hotline 
on that one he said 
