bishop in august approved what was called the great compromise 
passed by an an overwhelming majority of 423 to 28 the bishops 
of the 28 branches including both proponents and opponents of 
female clergy upheld the right of each branch to decide for itself 
whether to consecrate women bishops 
the measure calls for mutual respect between branches which 
disagree on the issue and exercise of courtesy between bishops of 
differing opinions conference resolution are not binding but 
carry much weight among members 
an international commission was authorized to work out means to 
hold the communion together once a woman was conscrated a bishop 
