the election was one more victory for the peripatetic americans 
who are finding more and more work these days as advisers to 
foreign political campaigns 
for 20 years americans have traveled the world to help 
candidates in both fledgling and longstanding democracies decide 
which issues are the key to success in their races they also tutor 
them in the latest us electioneering techniques and technology 
sensitive to any suggestion that they change the nature of the 
political systems they intervene in us campaign firms and 
advisers keep a low profile but americans have been deeply 
involved in national elections in more than 30 nations including 
australia canada panama spain britain france ireland 
nigeria mexico the philippines japan and greece 
