longtime newsman rich heiland of 
arlington has been named publisher of the huntsville item the 
newspaper announced 
heiland 42 most recently was urban affairs writer and 
columnist for the fort worth startelegram and is a former editor 
and publisher for dallasfort worth suburban newspapers a 
subsidiary of the ah belo corp 
heiland succeeds steve balke as publisher of the newspaper owned 
by thomson newspapers 
he began his newspaper career in 1972 as a reporter for the 
xenia ohio daily gazette which received a pulitzer prize for 
coverage of a tornado that struck the town in 1974 
in 1976 heiland became managing editor of the piqua ohio 
daily call and in 1978 became editorpublisher of the newspaper 
in 1979 he was named publisher of the macomb ill daily journal 
he joined the dallasfort worth newspapers in 1982 
in 198485 he was named top serious columnist in the nation for 
newspapers with circulation less than 15000 in the national 
newspaper associations better newspaper contest 
heiland has won several ohio illinois and texas associated 
press awards for writing texas united press international writing 
and design awards and additional honors from the dallas press club 
a graduate of wilmington college in ohio heiland also taught 
news writing and reporting at western illinois university 
he is currently enrolled as a graduate student in urban 
administration in the university of texas at arlingtons institute 
of urban studies 
