he said the threecity service would be renamed the trump 
shuttle and its bluesilver boeing 727s would be redecorated and 
emblazoned with red black and gold stripes 
the deal is expected to be completed by middecember if it 
survives government scrutiny and a legal attack by easterns unions 
easterns militant union leaders said the sale would be the 
death of the airline and vowed a fight to overturn the deal 
the announcement of the sale followed a week of speculation 
about the billionaire developers interest in buying the shuttle 
from ailing eastern which is a major subsidiary of texas air 
the 365 million price tag was well above previous estimates of 
what trump would pay 
its top dollar said robert joedicke an airline analyst 
for the investment firm shearson lehman hutton inc 
many analysts and other observers had estimated that the shuttle 
which serves new york boston and washington and is the most 
profitable of easterns operations could fetch from 200 million 
to 300 million texas air had tried earlier this year to transfer 
the shuttle operation from eastern to a new subsidiary for 225 
million but eastern unions blocked that attempt 
standard amp poors corp in announcing that it was keeping a 
close eye on eastern in the wake of the shuttle sale said the 365 
million was a generous price the interest on that sum could 
recover more than half the cash flow that would be lost by selling 
the shuttle the creditrating agency said 
for the flamboyant and imageconscious trump the purchase of 
the shuttle could be viewed more as a way to enhance his prestige 
and influence than a straight business deal 
earlier this year trump bought the legendary plaza for 400 
million following a heated battle with other suitors trump has 
admitted that he was in love with the hotel for more than a 
decade and tore himself up to get it 
but there also could be compelling business logic behind trumps 
latest acquisition many analysts said trump might use the shuttle 
to help draw people to his hotel and casino properties in atlantic 
city nj on the weekends 
its something that were looking at trump said at the news 
conference 
trump now operates a helicopter service from new york to 
atlantic city the resort citys bader field is too small to handle 
the boeing 727s operated by the shuttle but the atlantic city 
airport 10 miles from the city can accommodate them 
trump noted a report that he intended to sell the land earmarked 
for a huge commercial development in manhattan to help finance the 
shuttle deal but he did not directly address its accuracy no 
interested party could afford to pay him what the 100acre site is 
worth he joked to reporters 
trump and lorenzo said the shuttle would maintain fares 
competitive with the competing shuttle service of pan am corp and 
would not lay off any employees the 365 million price tag 
includes landing rights at airports in the three shuttle cities 
plus 17 planes 
pan am said it welcomed trump into the shuttle market pan am 
claims its share of that market has jumped from around 24 percent 
in october 1986 to roughly 45 percent 
eastern spokesman robin matell said late wednesday that the 
airlines shuttle service had net income of around 168 million in 
1987 on revenue of 403 million down from a 1985 profit of 282 
million on revenue of 492 million pan am has not disclosed 
earnings from its shuttle operations 
the shuttle deal marks another tumultuous chapter in the saga of 
eastern the miamibased carrier that has been scarred by 
managementlabor feuding and 1 billion in losses over the past 
decade 
i think the sale was inevitable you could see it coming 
said frank borman the former astronaut and chairman of eastern 
the inevitable problem at eastern has been a very recalcitrant 
union leadership borman said in a telephone interview from las 
cruces nm where he works as an aviation consultant 
he said 365 million was a fair price for the shuttle 
</TEXT>
