first city bancorporation of texas inc in its 
first quarterly report since a 16 billion restructuring earlier 
this year on wednesday announced a 236 million thirdquarter 
profit 
earnings for the three months ended sept 30 were in line with 
the companys forecast of 98 million in net income for the first 
12 months of operation said a robert abboud first citys 
chairman and chief executive officer 
the forecast assumes gradually increasing earnings through the 
period abboud said 
the thirdquarter earnings amount to 97 cents per share 
compared with net income of 172 million or 70 cents per share 
for a shortened reporting period running from april 20 through june 
30 
first city was bailed out in april with 970 million in 
assistance from the federal deposit insurance corp a spinoff of 
179 billion and possibly more in poorly performing assets and 
a 500 million capital infusion from an investor group headed by 
abboud 
the houstonbased bank holding company with 62 banks in texas 
and one in south dakota grew quickly during the texas oil boom 
but was hard hit by energy and real estate losses when oil prices 
plummeted first city also has branches in london singapore and 
nassau and representative offices in hong kong and tokyo 
